news.title: Kalpataru reports net loss of Rs 100.74 crore in FY24
news.para: Mumbai-based Kalpataru Ltd has filed the draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) to launch its IPO, which comprises a fresh issue of shares, having a face value of Rs 10 each, aggregating up to Rs 1,590 crore.

news.title: Four listed REITs distribute Rs 1,371 crore to unitholders in Q1 FY24
news.para: Indian REITs Association (IRA) data showed that in the latest June quarter, these four REITs have together distributed more than Rs 1,371 crore to over 2,45,000 unit holders.

news.title: Australia's Dexus reports annual loss of $1.5 billion in FY24
news.para: Dexus' A$14.8 billion ($9.9 billion) portfolio of offices and warehouses shrank 12.9% or A$1.9 billion in value over the year ended in June.

news.title: Rajokri residents block bulldozers, seek legal relief on demolitions from Delhi HC
news.para: Residents of Rajokri village near Vasant Kunj successfully blocked attempts by forest officials to demolish their homes. The locals, who have lived there for over three decades, have valid documents and claim the right to rehabilitation. They are now seeking a stay on demolitions from the Delhi High Court.

news.title: Goa HC dismisses appeal against demolition of illegal structures
news.para: Although the area covered by the structures could be considered small, once found to be illegal, he cannot take advantage of it, the high court observed.

news.title: New Zealand house prices fall 1.4% in July: REINZ report
news.para: The same seasonally adjusted figures show a sales increase of 6.4% compared to June, and an increase of 5.4% compared to July 2023.

news.title: China's Kaisa Group, bondholders agree to restructure offshore debt
news.para: The Shenzhen-based developer has been working to restructure its offshore debt since defaulting on $12 billion in offshore bonds in late 2021. The restructuring plan also covers other debts including loans and yuan-denominated asset-backed securities.

news.title: Australia's ANZ Group sees increase in late home loan payments
news.para: Mortgage payments past due date for 90 days or more rose 5 basis points from the March quarter to 84 bps for ANZ Group's Australian housing loans, the lender said in a limited quarterly trading update without disclosing its cash profit.

news.title: Trial run for Bengaluru's green line metro extension begins
news.para: The existing Metro line, which currently extends from Silk Board to Nagasandra, is now being extended to Madavara, near the Bangalore International Exhibition Centre.

news.title: Nothing to do with transfer of common area: Registrar of cooperative societies in Karnataka
news.para: This particular response from the Registrar of Cooperative Societies’ is suggesting that the state government is not committed to enabling the Real Estate Regulatory Authority-Karnataka (RERA) to effectively function for the benefit of home buyers.

news.title: SC-appointed panel orders action on encroachments in Delhi
news.para: “After the coaching institute incident in Old Rajendra Nagar and, on the basis of several ongoing court cases of illegal construction related to Narela, central zones, etc., the activity of the monitoring committee has increased,” said an MCD official.

news.title: Chandigarh: UMTA to meet on September 2 to discuss tricity metro project
news.para: Notice of the meeting, along with schedule and agenda, has been sent to all members of UMTA, mainly state governments of Punjab, Haryana and Himachal Pradesh.

news.title: Thailand's Ratanarak Group takes control of Siam City by buying Jardine Cycle's stake
news.para: Under the deal, Ratanarak unit Sunrise Equity bought 76.1 million shares in Siam City for 160 baht apiece, valuing the cement manufacturer at 47.68 billion baht.

news.title: Sebi issues guidelines for borrowing by category I & II alternative investment funds
news.para: These alternative investment funds (AIFs) are allowed to borrow funds to address temporary funding needs or manage day-to-day operational expenses, with specific limitations.

news.title: Navi Mumbai international airport is moving along pretty quick: Cristiano Ceccato, Zaha Hadid Architects
news.para: In conversation with Ankit Sharma of ETRealty, Cristiano Ceccato, director, Zaha Hadid Architects (ZHA), which had been appointed as the architect of NMIA following an international design competition, talked about the design plans of the project and opportunities they see in India.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body set to demolish 10-floor illegal building
news.para: A 10-storey building in Kalyan, Yusuf Height, was determined to be illegally constructed on land designated for a garden and night shelter. After monsoon, KDMC plans to demolish it. The Thane police's EOW filed a complaint against the builder, Salman Dolare, and accomplices for using fake permissions and causing governmental revenue losses.

news.title: Smartworks Coworking Spaces reports Rs 50 crore loss in FY24
news.para: According to the DRHP, the company's net loss stood at Rs 49.95 crore in the 2023-24 fiscal, down 50 per cent from Rs 101 crore in the preceding financial year.

news.title: Madurai civic body suspends five bill collectors for property tax fraud
news.para: The Madurai corporation suspended five bill collectors for decreasing property tax assessments, leading to a revenue loss of Rs 1 crore over two years. The officials were found guilty of accepting bribes to lower taxes without proper authorization. Commissioner C Dinesh Kumar revealed the fraud after an inquiry and called for stringent audits to prevent future irregularities.
